  <body>
    <segment id="1" parent="2" relname="means">I need my neighbor&apos;s children to be okay </segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="18" relname="span">
so that my children will be okay.</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="15" relname="list">
I need all of my neighbor’s children to be okay, 
poor inner city children in Atlanta and poor children of Appalachia, </segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="15" relname="list">
I need the poor children of Israel and the poor children of Gaza, </segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="15" relname="list">
I need Israelis and Palestinians, </segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="15" relname="list">
I need those in the Congo, those in Haiti, those in Ukraine, </segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="15" relname="list">
I need American children on both sides of the track to be okay. </segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="17" relname="span">
Because we are all God’s children. </segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="16" relname="list">
And so let’s stand together. </segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="16" relname="list">
Let’s work together. </segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="16" relname="list">
Let’s organize together. </segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="16" relname="list">
Let’s pray together. </segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="16" relname="list">
Let’s stand together. </segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="16" relname="list">
Let’s heal the land.</segment>
